reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful phone and excellent price...
reviews.reviewText: Beautiful phone and excellent price. Sadly, I had to return it. T-Mobile has a weak signal in the area where I live. The UMIDIGI F3 SE phone (which is 4G LTE) would not pick up / ring on an incoming calls while I am inside my home or nearby. A few miles away where the T-Mobile signal is stronger, the phone rings on incoming calls. Outgoing calls, in/out SMS, and WIFI work fine. When I transferred the SIM card to a 5G phone that I borrowed, the 5G phone picked up / rang on incoming calls hile I am inside my home or nearby. UMIDIGI sent me instructions to test and capture and share the log file. I did. UMIDIGI is investigating. I hope they will figure out the problem. In my specific case, a 5G phone seems to be the solution.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Couldn't make or receive calls
reviews.reviewText: This is a good phone. Lightweight and thin. Email, texting, internet worked fine. I spent a lot of time texting, emailing, messaging and talking to Mint Mobile and Amazon IT. To no avail. Finally, I returned the first phone and received a replacement. Right out of the box it had the same issue. No calling out and could not receive calls. I'm waiting now to hear from Umidigi. I want this phone to work so badly but I'm thinking that won't happen. If it functioned like a cell phone is supposed to I would give it 4 stars. The battery seems to drain quickly and the camera isn't that great but I always have a charger nearby and I don't take a lot of pictures.
Good price. Heavy ! I used it as a back up phone.

reviews.reviewText: Telefono che perde sempre il segnale, provato sia con SIM iliad e windtre e Vodafone, risultato: doverlo riavviare di continuo...
